<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Turkey-Kurds     05-28 0129</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Turkey-Kurds,0132</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Four Kurdish Guerrillas, Two Policemen Killed In Clash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KIGI, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four men thought to be Kurdish guerrillas
and two police officers were killed in a clash in this township 590
miles east of Ankara, Hurriyet news agency reported Friday.
   The guerrillas responded to calls to surrender with a volley of
fire after they were surrounded in a joint police-military
operation near Kilise hamlet in Dogucak village late Thursday, the
agency said.
   The dispatch said a major and three other security forces
members were wounded.
   Hurriyet said the guerrillas were believed to belong to the
Kurdish Labor Party, which seeks to set up a Marxist state in parts
of eastern and southeastern Turkey.
   Ethnic Kurds make up about one-fifth of Turkey's population of
52 million.
</TEXT>
