<1ST_LINE>r a PM-SexCheats     05-28 0205</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Sex Cheats,0210</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>University Students Caught Cheating on Sex Exam</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The human sexuality class at San Francisco
State University is in an uproar over cheating, and some students
could be flunked or expelled, university officials say.
   The final examination for the class _ the school's most popular
course _ has been tossed out because some students cheated,
officials said.
   ``I guess they don't want to run home and say they flunked
sex,'' said student discipline officer Robert Westwood.
   At midweek, Westwood said, at least 10 students of a class of
700 were caught taking the final with duplicate copies marked with
the correct answers. The test was halted and declared void. A
makeup test was scheduled later.
   Some students told school officials that copies of the test had
been floating around the campus for about a week before the exam.
One student said the copies were being hawked out of a car.
   Teacher Ann Auleb said she was furious to discover the cheating,
theorizing tht some students apparently found the class too
demanding.
   ``Many students come to this course thinking they know
everything about human sexuality,'' she said. ``They find out they
don't, so they find an easy way out.''
</TEXT>
