<HEAD>Woman Arrested After Boyfriend's Dismembered Body Found</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents may be offensive</NOTE>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 24-year-old man was killed and dismembered in
his girlfriend's apartment apparently after he threw the woman's
cat against the wall and punched a television screen, police said.
   Lori McLuckie, 26, was arrested Friday after the dismembered
body was found on the living room floor of her apartment, police
said.
   McLuckie, who is pregnant, was jailed for investigation of
first-degree murder and ordered held without bond.
   The man's identity was withheld until relatives could be
notified, but authorities said he was a Denver resident.
   Detective Calvin Hemphill said police were called to the
apartment on a tip and found the victim's torso and head on a piece
of plastic on the floor. A search turned up the victim's limbs,
wrapped in plastic bags and deposited in several trash bins in the
neighborhood.
   Police believe the man was stabbed to death, possibly with a
kitchen knife, and then was dismembered.
   ``It was a very grotesque scene,'' said Detective Capt. James
Fitzpatrick.
   Police said they were told by an unidentified informant that the
victim was stabbed to death after a violent argument in which he
grabbed McLuckie's cat and threw it against the wall, then swung
his fist into the television set.
