<DATELINE>WEBSTER, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Houston Astros player Cesar Cedeno
was arrested on charges of assault, causing bodily injury and
resisting arrest after an attack on a woman identified as his
girlfriend and the mother of his child.
   The former outfielder was intoxicated and apparently angry over
custody of his 4-month-old daughter, said Webster Police Chief
Reyes Sonora.
   Pam Lamon, 32, was treated for bruises by ambulance personnel
and refused to be taken to a hospital, he said.
   ``It took three or four officers to put him in the car,'' Sonora
said. ``He was very belligerent.''
   Cedeno, 37, has had a series of run-ins with the law during and
after his 12-year career with the Astros. In 1974 he was convicted
of manslaughter and fined $100 in his native Dominican Republic for
shooting to death a 19-year-old woman.
   Cedeno was released Friday on $2,000 bail. He told police he is
unemployed.
