<HEAD>Thunderstorm Causes Havoc In Rome Area</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A violent thunderstorm hit Rome and adjacent coastal
towns Saturday, flooding roads, disrupting air traffic and trapping
people in their cars, including a woman driving to her wedding.
   In the town of Fiumicino, near Leonardo da Vinci international
airport, the bride, dressed in her wedding gown, had to be rescued
by firefighters and taken to the church in a fire truck.
   Several domestic flights and a flight from Hong Kong had to be
rerouted from Rome to other airports in Italy because of the rain.
Firefighters had to rescue a number of passengers blocked in the
international arrivals parking lot.
   Flood waters reached nearly five feet in parts of the nearby
seaside town of Ostia.
