<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Colombia-Assassination     05-28 0164</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Colombia-Assassination,0168</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gunmen Kill Leftist Leaders, Bodyguard</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VILLAVICENCIO, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Assailants opened fire with
submachine guns in a pizza parlor and killed two leftist leaders
and a bodyguard, police said Saturday.
   The attack in this central town Friday night killed Carlos
Batista, the leader of the assembly in Meta state; Nestor Henry
Rojas, a former mayoral candidate in the town of Puerto Gaitan; and
Jose Antonio Riveras, a bodyguard, Villavencio police said in a
news release.
   All three men were members of the leftist Patriotic Union.
   In the past two years, right-wing death squads have allegedly
killed about 550 members of the Patriotic Union, in addition to
hundreds more peasants, teachers, university students and
sympathizers of leftist causes in Colombia.
   The Patriotic Union has accused the army of controlling the
death squads, but Defense Minister Rafael Samudio has denied the
accusation.
   Villavicencio, the capital of Meta state, is at the foot of the
Andes, 45 miles southeast of the capital of Bogota.
</TEXT>
