<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--NevadaQuake     05-28 0159</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Nevada Quake,0162</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Small Quake Jolts Boulder City, Nev.; No Damage Reported</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOULDER CITY, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An earthquake jostled part of southern
Nevada early Saturday but there were no reports of damage or
injuries, authorities said.
   The quake, measuring 3.2 on the Richter scale and centered five
miles southwest of Boulder City, struck at 3:51 a.m., said John
Minsch of the U.S. Geological Survey's earthquake information
center in Golden, Colo.
   ``We had reports that it was felt in the Boulder City area, but
no reports of any damage,'' Minsch said. Boulder City is a town of
9,600 about 10 miles southeast of Las Vegas.
   The quake struck an area that has experienced several small
temblors in the past six months, he said.
   The Richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an
earthquake, as measured by the ground motion recorded on a
seismograph. A quake measuring 3.5 on the scale is capable of
slight damage.
</TEXT>
