<2ND_LINE>AM-Obit-Townsend,0133</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Olympic Skier, Williams College Coach Dies at 66</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILLIAMSTOWN, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robert J. Townsend, a member of the
National Ski Hall of Fame and ski coach at Williams College for 22
years, has died at age 66, the college announced Saturday.
   Townsend died Friday at North Adams Regional Hospital, the
college said.
   Townsend overcame war injuries to compete at the 1948 Winter
Olympics and won the U.S. nordic skiing championship in 1947 and
1949. He coached skiing at Williams from 1950-72, and was assistant
coach of football and lacrosse.
   As secretary to the U.S. Olympic Ski Games Committee, Townsend
helped select the U.S. ski teams for the 1960 and 1964 games.
   He is survived by his wife, Harriet; a daughter; two sons, and
two grandchildren.
</TEXT>
