<HEAD>Japanese Cop Robbed Bank to Buy Girlfriend a House</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 25-year police veteran accused not only of
robbing a bank, but doing it while on duty, told investigators he
wanted to buy a house for his girlfriend, police said Saturday.
   Katsutoshi Yamane, a 46-year-old assistant inspector, was
arrested Friday afternoon soon after taking $22,000 from the Saga
Credit Bank brance in Tosu, western Japan.
