<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Cuba-RedCross     05-28 0104</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Cuba-Red Cross,0106</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Red Cross Team To Visit Cuban Jails</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A commission from the International Committee
of the Red Cross will inspect conditions in Cuban jails beginning
Monday, the Cuban government's Prensa Latina news agency said
Saturday.
   In a dispatch monitored in Mexico City, Prensa Latina said four
Red Cross inspectors will be permitted to meet with several
``counterrevolutionary prisoners'' during the trip.
   The agency said 323 people are imprisoned ``for crimes against
the security of the state.''
   The inspection tour was arranged during an April visit to Cuba
by Cornelio Sommaruga, president of the Red Cross' international
committee.
</TEXT>
