<HEAD>Heathrow Maintenance Workers End Strike</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   British Airway's 3,000 maintenance workers at
Heathrow Airport ended a five-day strike Friday.
   In a mass meeting, the workers agreed to an independent
assessment of their grievances over dismissal of a shop steward,
airline and union officials said.
   British Airways maintained near-normal operations throughout the
dispute, using a skeleton management staff.
   There was concern earlier that the strike might disrupt flights
over the three-day weekend. Monday is a bank holiday in Britain.
